27 years ago on June 25th 1996 I released my album “Keith Sweat” off of Elektra Records.  The Album sold over 4 million copies & the Singles Twisted & Nobody has sold over 8 million copies alone .  The single Twisted peaked #1 on Billboard Rhythmic Top 40 charts.. I can’t thank my fans enough for their continued support over the years…. Big shoutout to my guy @_thamarvelous1 on this one…Celebrate with me as we continue this journey …….Let’s see how many fans still have my cd or record in their collection !!!!!!!!!! #keithsweat #rnb #newjackswing #twisted #nobody

I really do appreciate you all. Every time I hit that stage I make sure I give you all  1000%. social_posts.post_text: Today I am Thankful to be able to celebrate 35 years of my album release ‘Make It Last Forever’ .. This has been an amazing journey through the years and I appreciate every moment I am still able to share on the stage with all of my fans.  I want to thank all of you for your continued support and I promise you all, every time I touch the stage me and my team will never disappoint.  Thank you all again …I am so blessed for each and every one  of you..

And that’s a wrap ….Final show of 2023 … Pueblo Colorado thank you for having me and coming out and showing me so much love.. This year has been amazing with all the cities I was able to bless.  2024 is only going to get better.. Working on some big things for the new year.  New Show, new projects and so much more…. Tune in and watch what I have in store for you all.
